pageMetadata.prefillForCoverLetter:
Dear Software Team Hiring Manager,

This letter is to express my interest in your posting on Indeed.com for a Full Stack Web Developer. With extensive hands-on experience in React, Next.js, MongoDB, and SQL. I am confident I will be an asset to your organization.

I enjoy the challenge of working with new technologies and people that push me outside of my comfort zone and existing knowledge. I believe that consistently learning and developing new techniques is vital to my own success and the success of your company.
Your listed requirements closely match my background and skills. A few I would like to highlight that would enable me to contribute to your bottom line are:

-Experience working in a team environment under a skilled architect.
-Understanding of communicating with Mongo databases using REST APIs.
-Hands-on Javascript and related frameworks expertise.
-Knowledge of front-end and back-end development best practices.
-Comprehension of troubleshooting techniques.
-SQL database administration for a fortune 100 company


Thank you for your time and consideration. I look forward to speaking with you about this opportunity.

Sincerely,

Zachary Barnes

pageMetadata.jobDescription:
About us

As the World’s Largest Pool League, American Poolplayers Association (APA) has a unique business model that brings the people who are passionate about pool together with those who want to be social and have fun into a perfect mix of sports-themed entertainment. Only under our exceptional system can people from all backgrounds and skill levels, from total beginners to semi-professional, compete in the game of pool and have fun.

About You:

You bring experience from working with Agile development teams, where you've played a crucial role in testing. Your enthusiasm lies in automating testing whenever possible and maintaining those tests while efficiently managing manual testing. Testing software is not just a job; it's a passion for you. Your ultimate goal is to seamlessly integrate testing into the development process and guarantee flawless feature execution in production.

You take a tremendous amount of ownership in the testing processes and procedures, but you are not afraid to ask for some help when there's too much to do and so little time to do it in. You know your way around a database because sometimes it takes some digging into the data to know where an issue really is.

Is the problem you've found an issue with the code, a data issue, a deployment issue? You have just enough know how to figure this out so you can send the issue to the right person with enough detail to point them in the right direction.

About the Role:

  • Balance manual and automated testing to ensure comprehensive test coverage
  • Design and develop automated test cases for web, iOS, and Android applications
  • Conducting functional, integration, regression, and performance testing
  • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into test scenarios
  • Conduct root cause analysis of defects and work with developers/BA's to resolve issues
  • Document test results and provide recommendations for improvements
  • Stay updated with industry best practices and emerging technologies in software testing
  • Applicants will be evaluated for either full-time employment or a consultant role, contingent upon the alignment of needs between APA and the applicant.

Your experience:

  • Proven experience creating automated test cases for web, iOS, and Android applications
  • Exceptional teamwork and communication skills
  • Strong knowledge of software development life cycle (SDLC) and testing methodologies
  • Experience with test automation tools such as Cypress and Playwright is highly desirable
  • May have experience with Chai and Mocha assertions

About Us:

As the World’s Largest Pool League, the American Poolplayers Association (APA) has a unique business model that brings the people who are passionate about pool together with those who want to be social and have fun into a perfect mix of sports-themed entertainment.

We have a very relaxed atmosphere to work in and we believe in a healthy work/life balance. The APA is a family owned and operated business. The sense of family is very strong given that the average tenure of our employees is 10+ years.

If you've read this far, you might be thinking, "Some of that does sound like me. But, 'Your heart's desire?' Seriously?" We get it; we know you have other interests. However, we're ONLY seeking individuals who are passionate about software testing and can help us improve our testing process.

So what's in it for you?

Perks of working for APA:

  • We close our offices between Christmas and New Year (paid time off for full-time employees)
  • We embrace remote personnel and have developed a culture that supports remote work
  • Full Benefits package for full-time employees
  • Fun, friendly environment where you can be yourself, grow and learn with us.

If that sounds like you, please provide a cover letter and resume in PDF form.

Applicant must live in Continental United States.

Job Types: Full-time, Contract

Pay: $85,000.00 - $110,000.00 per year

Benefits:

  • 401(k)
  • 401(k) matching
  • Dental insurance
  • Flexible spending account
  • Health insurance
  • Life insurance
  • Paid time off
  • Vision insurance

Compensation package:

  • 1099 contract
  • Yearly pay

Experience level:

  • 3 years

Schedule:

  • 8 hour shift

Experience:

  • SQL: 2 years (Required)
  • Test automation: 3 years (Required)
  • Cypress: 1 year (Preferred)

Work Location: Remote
